Ahmet Davutolu is a Turkish politician and scholar who served as the Prime Minister of Turkey from 2014 to 2016. He held this position for a total of two terms. In addition to that, he served as Minister of Foreign Affairs from 2009 to 2014 and as a Member of Parliament for the district of Konya from 1999 until 2018. His foreign policy of "zero difficulties with neighbors" intended to strengthen Turkey's relations with the nations that are located in its immediate vicinity and earned him widespread recognition. 